title: Japanese Yen LIBOR Three Month Rate
description: Japanese Yen LIBOR Three Month Rate was at -0.03 percent on Monday November 7. Interbank Rate in Japan averaged 1.34 percent from 1986 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 8.50 percent in September of 1990 and a record low of -0.13 percent in March of 2020. The three month Yen LIBOR interest rate is the average interest rate at which a LIBOR contributor bank can obtain unsecured funding in the London interbank market for a three month period in Japanese Yen. This page provides - Japan Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: ICE
